div1.p: IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF FLETCHER DECKER FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS AND A WRIT OF CERTIORARI : : : :
ORDER DISCHARGING WRIT AND WITHDRAWING EXHIBITS

IN THIS MATTER PETITION for a writ of certiorari and for writ of habeas corpus having heretofore being filed and order having been granted requesting J.M. Boyle, United States Marshal for the Western District of Washington, to show cause why a writ of habeas corpus should not be issued herein, and the writ having been issued on the 9th day of September, 1921, and the court having considered the evidence and having heard the argument of counsel thereon, and counsel for petitioner having on the 9th day of September, 1921, orally stated in court that the writ of certiorari should be dismissed and the matter be presented on habeas corpus;

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, ADJUDGED and DECREED that the said writ of habeas corpus be, and it is hereby, discharged, and that the petitioner remain in the custody of the said J.M. Boyle, Marshal, to await the extradition mandate of the Secretary of State.
AND IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the United States Attorney may withdraw the exhibits attached to the return of the said United States Attorney.
DONE in open court this 14th day of September, 1921.
Jeremiah Neterer J U D G E.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON Northern DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
